    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i hear that, but \"manageable operational adjustments\" sounds a bit like a dismissive way to put it for someone actually trying to pay rent. isn't it more accurate to say that for many small shops, these increases are just unsustainable and actually end up hurting the very workers they're meant to help by causing layoffs?",
